---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Lutaro — Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Lutaro, the Sony camera Picture Profile manager for iOS, iPadOS, and macOS."
>
  <h1>Lutaro Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="meta">Effective 2 July 2026</p>

  <p>
    Lutaro is an app for managing Sony camera Picture Profiles on iPhone,
    iPad, and Mac. The short version:
    <strong>Lutaro collects no data about you.</strong> There are no accounts,
    no analytics, no tracking, no ads, and no servers of ours — nothing you do
    in the app is sent to us or to any third party.
  </p>

  <h2>Data we collect</h2>
  <p>
    None. Lutaro has no analytics or telemetry of any kind and never phones
    home.
  </p>

  <h2>Your profile library</h2>
  <p>
    The Picture Profiles, tags, folders, and preview images you create are
    stored on your device. If you enable iCloud on your device, the library
    can sync through <em>your own</em> iCloud account (Apple's iCloud
    Documents); that data is handled by Apple under
    <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/">Apple's privacy policy</a>
    and is never visible to us.
  </p>

  <h2>Camera connections and credentials</h2>
  <p>
    Lutaro talks directly to your Sony camera over your local Wi-Fi network
    or USB. Camera passwords are stored in the device Keychain; connection
    metadata (such as a camera's name and identifiers) is stored on your
    device. Credentials are sent only to your camera during connection —
    never anywhere else.
  </p>

  <h2>Local network access</h2>
  <p>
    The app asks for local-network permission solely to discover and connect
    to your Sony camera on your Wi-Fi network. It does not scan for, connect
    to, or collect information about any other devices.
  </p>

  <h2>Photo library access</h2>
  <p>
    If you choose a sample image for a profile, the app reads only the photo
    you pick. It never browses or uploads your photo library.
  </p>

  <h2>Diagnostics</h2>
  <p>
    Lutaro can produce a diagnostics report to help troubleshoot camera
    connections. Reports are created only when you ask for one, are redacted
    by default (network addresses and serial numbers removed), and never
    leave your device unless you export and share them yourself.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    If this policy changes materially, the updated version will be published
    at this address with a new effective date.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions or concerns? Open an issue at
    <a href="https://github.com/tarakanof/Lutaro-Site/issues">github.com/tarakanof/Lutaro-Site/issues</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
